# Backend Standards

Details: Constitution §9, §19, §20; `docs/technical-architecture.md`.

- **Five-layer contexts** with inward dependencies; vendor SDKs only in adapters.
- **Dependency Injection** at the edge (no implicit module globals). Wire in `shared/platform`.
- **Routers are thin:** translate HTTP ↔ application use cases. No business logic, no SQL, no LLM calls.
- **Typed everything** (full type hints). No untyped dicts crossing boundaries. Validate inputs at the boundary (Pydantic).
- **Typed config** via pydantic-settings, per environment, fail-fast on missing values. No magic literals.
- **Errors:** typed domain errors → mapped to problem-details responses. Never leak stack traces/internals. Never swallow exceptions.
- **Logging:** structured JSON, correlation/trace id per line, PII-redacted. No `print`. No logging as flow control.
- **Long-running / AI work runs in `worker`**, enqueued via the `TaskQueue` port. Workers are idempotent with backoff + dead-letter.
- **Emit domain events** for cross-context state changes; never reach into another context.
- **No hardcoded secrets/model names/prompts.**
